          "candidate_value": "legal disclaimer If you have multiple bank accounts, you could receive a different monthly fee rebate for each account, as long as you meet the eligibility requirements to receive each of the rebates",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-e7f1c92f9f0ee368",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Top Bank Account Questions\nNo, you can only receive one monthly fee rebate per bank account. For example, you cannot receive both the Value Program Rebate legal disclaimer 14 and the Seniors Rebate legal disclaimer 13 on the same account in the same month. We automatically apply to your account the highest value rebate you are eligible for each month.\nlegal disclaimer\nIf you have multiple bank accounts, you could receive a different monthly fee rebate for each account, as long as you meet the eligibility requirements to receive each of the rebates.\nNo, RBC Vantage isn\u2019t a bank account\u2014it describes all of the powerful benefits you get with any eligible RBC bank account.\nAvion Rewards gives you the opportunity to earn Avion points in many ways and the flexibility to redeem them for nearly endless options\u2014travel the world, buy merchandise and gift cards from some of your favourite brands,",
