          "evidence_text_excerpt": "e their own limits.\nAt RBC, there\u2019s no limit on the number of HISAs you can open.\nGenerally, you cannot lose money in a high interest savings account. While interest rates can fluctuate, your principal will stay the same, minus service fees for any transactions you make on the account. Your principal is protected by the Canada Deposit Insurance Corporation (CDIC), a federal Crown corporation that insures eligible deposits and protects your savings in case of a financial institution failure.\nLike other types of savings accounts, the interest rate for the RBC High Interest eSavings account is subject to change based on market conditions.\nFrom time to time, RBC may also offer a promotional rate for the RBC High Interest eSavings account .\nWith an RBC High Interest eSavings account , you earn interest on every dollar you save. Interest is calculated daily and paid monthly to grow your",
